<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900713-0054</DOCNO><DOCID>900713-0054.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Genlyte Group Inc.:   Firm Reports Its Earnings   In Second Period Fell 51%</HL><DATE>07/13/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B8</SO><CO>   GLYT</CO><IN>EARNINGS (ERN)</IN><LP>   Genlyte Group Inc., Secaucus, N.J., reported thatsecond-quarter earnings dropped 51% on a 4.3% drop in sales.   The manufacturer of lighting fixtures and controls citedeffects of strikes in Canada, which have ended, and sluggishconstruction in the U.S. Genlyte said early in June that itexpected the declines.</LP><TEXT>   Net income sank to $1.7 million, or 13 cents a share, from$3.4 million, or 26 cents a share, a year earlier. Salesdropped to $123 million, from $128.5 million.   Strikes in Ontario halted construction from May 1 to July9, and shorter wildcat strikes were called in Quebec; theyseriously hurt Genlyte's results. The company expects toreturn to more normal operations this quarter.   Genlyte also reduced its debt by $2 million, to $162.5million.   In national over-the-counter trading yesterday, Genlyte'sshares fell 25 cents to close at $7.50.</TEXT></DOC>